comments: Held tool box meeting with involved personnel. Prepared equipment for skidding. Skidded rig from F-4 to F-14. Removed hatch on F-14.

Continued changing wires on aft PRS.  Meanwhile rigged tugger in moonpool for running DCI hose. Worked on releasing DCI hose connection. Came free at 19:00. Changed oil in TDS and cleaned pits. Stopped working on aft PRS due to high wind speed.
Removed hatches and built scaffolding/fence around open hatches on all levels on slot F-14. Recovered tugger for DCI hose.
LD 8 1/4" DC stand and jar.
LD 8 1/4" DC stand and jar.
WOW due to noe crane operation. Wind 45-50 knop, with gust up to 65 knop.

WOW due to noe crane operation. Wind 40-45 knop, with gusts up to 60 knop.

Meanwhile changed oil in TDS, adjusted fingerboard for CART stand, cleaned pits and carried on with rig maintenance.
Changed wash pipe and serviced TDS.
PU CART and MU to stand. RB in derrick.
PU 36" HO assembly. Removed master bushing and outer ring. RIH with 36" HO assembly to 9 m and re-instated outer ring and bushing. MU and RIH with 36" HO BHA from 9 m to 63 m.
Performed derrick inspection prior to spudding the hole. Special care were taken due to high winds of 40-50 knop.
MU and RIH with 36" HO BHA from 63 m to 93 m.
Stopped RIH due to power syncronisation interference with production/prosessmodul.

MU 36" BHA from 93 m to 143 m. Stung into funnel assisted by ROV. Observed fill in funnel and below. ROV had black-out on camera as soon as 17 1/2" bit had entered funnel. ROV went to surface for repairs. Continued RIH slowly without pumps and with no rotation until positive tag at 145.7 m.
Pumped SW at 550 lpm and washed down with no rotation to 148 m to allow centralizer drill bushing to land out in template guide-funnel.

Drilled 36" hole from 148 m to 150 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 550 lpm /  SPP 4-5 bar / 5 RPM / Torque 1-2 kNm / WOB  1 MT. Reamed hole to ensure landing of centralizer drill bushing in template guide-funnel.

Drilled 36" hole from 150 m  to 158 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 550-3100 lpm /  SPP 4-40 bar / 5-20 RPM / Torque 2-4 kNm / WOB 1-2 MT / ROP 5 m/hr. Pumped 20 m3 hi-vis pill prior to connection. Downlinked and performed survey at 145 m.

Survey at 145 m 0.3 inc

Drilled 36" hole from 158 m  to 193 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 4550 lpm /  SPP 80-82 bar / 90 RPM  / Torque 4-10 kNm / WOB 1-6 MT / ROP 15-20 m/hr. Pumped 20 m3 hi-vis pills prior to connection. Downlinked and performed survey at 154, 164 and 174 m. Up weight 103 MT / Down weight 96 MT.

Survey at 154 m 0.21 inc
            at 164 m 0,26 inc 
            at 174 m 0,37 inc

Drilled 36" hole from 193 m to 204 m 17 1/2" bit depth / 201 m 36" HO depth. Drilling parameters : Flow 4550 lpm /  SPP 80-82 bar / 90 RPM  / Torque 4-10 kNm / WOB 1-6 MT / ROP 15-20 m/hr. Pumped 20 m3 hi-vis pills prior to connection. Downlinked and performed survey at 184 m. 

Survey at 184 m 0.43 inc
Pumped 25 m3 hi-vis sweep and circulated btms up with SW. Displaced hole to 1.40 sg bentonite mud, Flow 5000 lpm /  SPP 140 bar / 30 RPM  / Torque 2 kNm.
POOH with 36" HO BHA from 204 m to 150 m. Topped up hole with 1.40 sg bentonite mud. Continued POOH with 36" HO BHA from 150 m to 9 m.
Removed master bushing and outer ring. POOH with 36" HO assembly and re-instated outer ring and bushing. LD 36" HO assembly.

WOW due to no crane operation. Wind 40 knop, with gusts up to 50 knop.

Meanwhile serviced TDS, greased manifolds on BOP, K/C, stand pipe manifolds and performed fluid ends inspection on MP2.
Changed elevator and bails. Installed 30" bushing. Prepared HTS.
Cleared rig floor.
Held pre-job meeting with all personnel involved. Prepared shoe joint and checked float for flow-through with SW. Painted shoe white. Continued to RIH with 30" conductor as per tally.

RIH with 30" conductor x-over joint and started installing cement top-up system with cement outlet 35 m below mud line. Aligned UWG top-up system to avoid conflict with the 3 hydraulic rams in the template well slot.
RIH with 30" conductor x-over joint and installing cement top-up system with cement outlet 35 m below mud line.
Changed 30" conductor bails and elevator to to 5 1/2" DP handling equipment.
Held pre-job meeting with involved personnel. Focused on weather conditions and running into splash zone. PU and installed 30" conductor housing joint.
WOW, due to high wind and waves. Wind 50-87 knop.
WOW, due to high wind, waves and hael. Wind 65-83 knop.
WOW due to high wind and waves.
WOW due to high wind and waves.
WOW. High wind and waves. Meanwhile performed rig maintenance.
Held a tool box meeting. Run the 30" conductor housing. Laid down the conductor running tool.
Run and made up the cementing stinger in the conductor.
Picke up CART housing. Installed 2" fill up valve. Installed inclinometer on CART.
Installed top up cement system on the 30" conductor pipe whlie running down. Foot injury on centraliser deck.
Investigated incident involving a service hand.
Continued to install top up cement system on the 30" conductor pipe whlie running down.
Run 30" conductor on 5 1/2" landing string.
Continued to run 30" conductor on 5 1/2" landing string. Problems with top drive torque wrench.
Problems with torque wrench on top drive. Not able to disconnect top drive from landing string.

Pulled back one single. Broke connection using the iron roughneck. Continued to RIH. Stabbed conductor into guide funnel at 03:30 hrs. Checked orientation of conductor shoe. Observed a broken connetion on the top up cement system. Continued to run the conductor to 160 m. Observed 20 tons weight. Worked conductor down to 169 m.

Made up the top drive and started to wash down from 169 m. Flow: 1000 ltr/min. SPP: 4 bar. Observed some of the cement top up piping no longer attached to the conductor pipe. Attempted to recover broken cement top up piping in the guide funnel.
Recovered broken off piece of top up cement piping.
Held tool box meeting with oncoming crew. Washed down with 30" conductor from 169 to 180 m, 1000 lpm.

Held a toolbox meeting. Rigged up tugger on centralizer deck and pulled conductor to starboard aft. Guided the conductor carefully through the guide funnel to 180.2 m to avoid further damage on top up cement piping. Washed down with 30" conductor from 180.2 m to 190 m, 1000 lpm. Observed leakage in top up cement piping at approx. 11 m below top housing.

Laid down top single at 190 m. Made up the cement stand. Washed down with the conductor to approx 40 cm above TD, 1000 lpm. Took digiquartz measurements. RIH and set conductor at TD 196.8 m. Confirmed top of housing 43 cm lower than F-7.
Prepared to activated the centralizers on the template using the ROV.

Held a tool box meeting regarding the cementing of the 30" conductor. Pressure tested the cementing line to 100 bar. Connected hot stab. Run centralizer sylinders on template and verified conductor position with ROV. Checked inclination: Roll 0.12, pitch 0.8.
Circulated 30 m3 of SW with 2500 lpm. Observed returns from slot F-14 came out of conductor annulus on slot F-7. Took time out, evaluated situation.
Held a tool box meeting prior to rig down the cement line.
Retracted centralizer dogs on template. Picked up 0,5 m  to confirm conductor free, free up weight 124 ton, no excess drag.
Attempted to confirm dogs fully retracted with ROV, not possible due to bad visibility.
WOW for visibillity to improve on the template.
Washed back to TD with conductor, 800 lpm.
WOW for visibility to improve on template.
WOW for visibility to improve on template. Unable to engage hot-stab for centraliser rams. Damaged claw for ROV arm. Came to surface with ROV to repare claw, dived again with ROV.
WOW for visibility to improve on template. Held meeting with essential personnel and went thought conductor cementing procedure.
WOW for visibility to improve on template.
WOW for visibility to improve on template. Meanwhile lined up and pressure tested the cement line to 100 bars. Stabbed hot-stab.

Worked with centralizer rams, rams were not working properlyy. Took out the hot-stab and flushed the lines, and stabbed the hot-stab back in, now the centralising rams worked properly. Retracted rams.
WOW for visibility to improve on template.
Held tool box talk prior to cementing of the 30" conductor.
Circulated SW at 250 lpm increased to 1000 lpm in 250 lpm steps. Still only returns coming out from F-7, hook load came down with 10 MT to 92 MT while pumping at 1000 lpm.

Pumped 30 m³ 1.7 SG mud, 1000 lpm, 5.7 bars, hookload dropped to 85 MT. Still only returns out from F-7. Picked up one meter with 120 MT and washed conductor back to setting depth, final hook load 76 MT. Total 20 m³ 1.7 SG mud pumped while washing down.
Started to take digiquartz measurement to confirm correct setting depth of the 30" conductor.

Picked up to original pick up weight of 120 MT 0.8 meter. Washed down conductor to correct setting depth at 196.8 meter, hook load 101 MT. Checked depth with digiquartz; 38 cm below F-7. Pumped 19 m³ of 1.7 SG mud, then 38 m³ sea water while washing down, return fluid up on nearby well, F-7.
Washed down 5 cm, and circulated/worked string until correct hookload, pumped a total of 216 m³ of sea water. Hook load 101 MT.  Return fluid up on nearby well, F-7.
Closed the centraliser Rams and verified same with the ROV. Checked depth with digiquartz; 43 cm below F-7.
Pumped 15 m³ 1.65 SG mud and applied 20 bars back pressure to IBOP.

Mixed and pumped 106 m³ 1.52 SG Tuned Light XL cement slurry, experienced problems with plugged lines towards the end. Pumped first 20 m3 at 600 lpm, then increased rate to 1000 lpm. Checked returns on F-7, only minor returns after 70 m³ pumped, got returns up F-14. Displaced cement slurry with 6.5 m³  SW with mud pumps. Hook load dropped from 101 to 99 MT during cement job.
Bled off pressure and checked for back-flow. Removed cement hose and flushed through manifolds and hoses.
Waited on cement to set. Meanwhile performed general maintenance.
Waited on cement to set. Meanwhile performed general maintenance.
Held tool box talk prior to pressure test of top-up system.
Lined up for flushing of top-up line.
Flushed top-up system and surface lines. Pressure tested UWG top-up system using the cement unit, rupture disk burst at 53 bars (769 psi).
Opened centralizer rams on F-14. Retrieved the hot stab from bank # 4.
Held tool box talk prior to perform top-up cement job.
Started to circulate with sea water 500 lpm. Performed cement top-up job, pumped 10.4 m³, 1.56 SG G-cement 82 bars at 500 lpm.

Flushed cement lines. Dropped 24 mm ball into the top-up hose, applied 240 bars to top-up to release the line NO-GO, bled down the pressure. Cut the hose using the ROV. Flushed lines and manifold on the rig floor and cement unit.

Checked inclinometer reading on the CART, opened the valve on the CART tool. Released the CART tool, slacked off to neutral weight = 76 MT, turned to the right 400/3000 Nm. Picked up the CART, tool weight 79 MT.  Laid out the cement pump in sub.

Held tool box prior to laying out the landing string. Laid out pup jnts. and HWDP landing string and checked serial numbers. Measured length using a laser measure, racked back landing string in derrick.
Problems with the PRS investigated same.
Continued POOH with landing string, measured same with laser.
Due to unusual noise from forward PRS, stop operation and performed full inspection of same.
Continued POOH with landing string, measured same with laser.
Held tool box talk prior to pull the master bushing, removed same. Pulled out the CART tool and removed the inclinometer, installed the master bushing.
Function tested and preserved the CART tool.
Held tool box talk, prior to measuring the landing string, and laying out the aluminium inner string.
Cleaned the rig floor.
Prepared for measuring the double on top of the CART tool. Laser measuring device was drop down onto the rig floor
Operation was terminated and an investigating was established. A statement of the incident was put together.
Held tool box talk, prior to measuring the landing string, and laying out the aluminium inner string. Measured the double.
Racked back the CART tool in derrick. Laid out the aluminium inner string.
Prepared for skidding of the cantilever from F-14 to F-5

Held toolbox talk prior to skidding rig from F-1 to F-14. Skidded rig 3 m starboard. Skidded rig/cantilever 6,5 m aft. Removed hatches in wellhead module on F-14. Ran stand of HWDP through rotary and made final adjustments.

Broke down stand of 5 1/2" HWDP and laid out three joints for backload and inspection. Rebuilt stand with 3 new joints of 5 1/2" HWDP and racked back in derrick. Ran tugger from moonpool to seabed to help ROV clear CTS hose.
Picked up 26" drilling BHA and brought to V-door. Meanwhile helped ROV to clear hose trapped below template using tugger.

Held toolbox talk prior to making up 26" drilling BHA. Removed masterbushing and ran 26" Bit / gMWD assy through rotary. Inserted gMWD probe in BHA as per Scientific instructions. Meanwhile ROV attempted to connect hose to CTS funnel. CTS hose was too short and the funnel had to be turned. ROV lost 3-finger claw when attempteing to turn CTS funnel.
Continued running BHA. Picked up and made up MWD/UBHO assy. Meanwhile pulled ROV to surface for repair.
Orientated UBHO sleeve as per Scientific instructions. Meanwhile repaired ROV manipulator claw.
Made up 3 x 9 1/2" NM DC to BHA and ran in to 63 m MD.  Repaired ROV and launched same. Assessed video recording from incident. Found 3-finger claw to be lost in hole. Assessed situation.
Laid out 1 x DC and made up hydro- mechanical jar to 8 1/4" DC stand. Racked back in derrick.  Discussed way forward with town.
Awaited further instuctions. Discussed way forward with town. Decided to run in with 26" rock bit BHA in attempt to remove junk in hole.
POOH with 26" drilling BHA. Racked back BHA in derrick. Laid out UBHO/MWD assy on deck.
Held toolbox talk prior to making up new 26" junk removal BHA with rock bit.
Made up 26" bit and bit sub to stand of 9 3/4" drillcollars. Removed masterbushing, ran stand through, installed masterbushing and hung off assy in rotary table.
Made up jar and 8 1/4" DC stand. Picked up single 8 1/4" DC and made up same.
RIH with 26" junk removal BHA on 5 1/2" HWDP from 70 m MD to 175 m MD. Stabbed into CTS on top of conductor housing while observing with ROV.
Washed down from 175 m to 183 m MD with 1000 lpm and tagged cement with 5 MT. Applied 4-6 MT WOB and rotated at 15 rpm down to 185 m MD.
POOH with 26 junk removal BHA from 185 m to just above CTS funnel at 138 m MD. ROV inspected 26" rock bit. No damage or junk could be observed.
Ran back in to 185 m MD to resume drilling cement. Connected CTS hose to ROV and started pumping with dredge pump.

Drilled cement from 185 m to 197 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 4400 lpm / SPP 62 bar / Rotation 45 rpm / Torque 1-3 kNm. Controlled penetration rate to 15 m/hrs. Observed higher WOB (autodrill 15 m/hr) from 193 m to 197 m MD indicating hard cement. 20 MT tonne WOB peak at 193 m MD and 3-10 MT downwards. Observed excessive rattling in string and WOB peaks around shoe depth at 197 m MD. Pumped 2 x 20 m3 hi-vis sweeps to clean hole.
Drilled rathole and shoe from 197 m to 201 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 4400 lpm / SPP 62 bar / Rotation 45 rpm / Torque 1-2 kNm / WOB 1-2 MT. Reamed back inside shoe for every 2 m drilled.
Drilled rathole and shoe from 197 m to 201 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 4400 lpm / SPP 62 bar / Rotation 45 rpm / Torque 1-6 kNm / WOB 1-8 MT. Reamed back inside shoe for every 2 m drilled.
Drilled 2 m new formation from 204 m to 206 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 4400 lpm / SPP 62 bar / Rotation 45 rpm / Torque 1-2 kNm / WOB 1-2 MT. Pumped 20 m3 his-vis sweep to clean hole.

POOH with 26" junk removal BHA from 206 m MD to surface on 5 1/2" HWDP. Laid down 1 x 8 1/4" DC. Racked back jar/DC assy. Lifted UBHO/MWD assy to HTS due to wind speed limitations on crane. Pulled 9 3/4" DC/bit stand to surface and inspected 26" rock bit. Found 2 x pieces of junk trapped in roller cones. Removed 1 piece of 800 g. The other piece was jammed in middle of the bit and could not be removed easily. Also found several worn teeth on bit.
Broke 26" bit and bit sub. Racked back stand of 9 3/4" DC.
Ran 26" drilling BHA from surface to 70 m MD.
Ran 26" drilling BHA from 70 m to 133 m MD.
RIH with 26" drilling BHA from 133 m to 206 m MD. Stabbed into CTS funnel while observing with ROV.

Established drilling parameters. Drilled 26" hole section from 206 m to 211 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3100 lpm / SPP 62 bar / 1-2 MT WOB / Rotation 125 RPM / String torque 1-3 kNm. Pumped 20 m3 hi-vis to clean the hole at 211 m MD. Scientifc drilling reported that UBHO sleeve had not been fastened correctly in the carrier. Decided to pull BHA for remedial action.
POOH with 26" drilling BHA from 211 m MD to 63 m MD. No drag observed when pulling BHA through conductor shoe. Racked back DC/jar and NMDC stands to access UBHO sub.
Checked UBHO relative to scribeline. Checked and thightened UBHO sleeve. Inspected 26" bit at Centralizer deck - no wear observed.
Made up and RIH with 26" drilling BHA from 63 m to 196 m MD. Stabbed into CTS funnel while observing with ROV.
Washed down with 26" drilling BHA from 196 m to 209 m MD pumping at 2000 lpm.
Performed singel shot survey on WL with bit inside conductor shoe. Inclination 0,33 deg / Azimuth 306,1 deg / Toolface 050 deg. Halted drilling operation for software upgrade on Siemens F&G system.
Stand-by for software upgrade of Siemens F&G system. At 18:15 hrs => Washed down to 209 m MD while pumping at 2000 lpm. Shut down pumps and waited for gMWD to reset.
Pumped at 2000 lpm and obtained gMWD survey - rejected survey.

Slided 26" drilling BHA from 211 m to 217 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3100 lpm / SPP 62 bar / 1-3 WOB / Rotation 95 RPM (bit rpm) / String torque 0-1 kNm. Pumped 10 m3 hi-vis sweep. Picked off bottom and hung off on slips.
Performed single shot survey on WL. Inclination 0,2 deg / Azimuth 243,9 deg / Toolface 112 deg. Pumped at 2000 lpm to obtain gMWD survey - rejected data.

Slided 26" drilling BHA from 217 m to 226 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3100 lpm / SPP 62 bar / 2-6 WOB / Rotation 95 RPM (bit rpm) / String torque 0-1 kNm. Pumped 10 m3 hi-vis sweep. Picked off bottom and hung off on slips.
Performed single shot survey on WL. Inclination 0,37 deg / Azimuth 297,4 deg / Toolface 112 deg. Pumped at 2000 lpm to obtain gMWD survey - rejected data.
Slided 26" drilling BHA from 226 m to 233 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3100 lpm / SPP 62 bar / 2-6 MT WOB / Rotation 95 RPM (bit rpm) / String torque 0-1 kNm.
Continued sliding from 233 m to 239 m MD. Pumped 10 m3 hi-vis sweep. Picked off bottom and hung off in slips.

Performed single shot survey on WL. Inclination 0,25 deg / Azimuth 320,5 deg / Toolface 125 deg. Adjusted toolface to 114 deg. Secured drillstring using chain hoist on Centralizer deck. Pumped at 2000 lpm to obtain gMWD survey - obatined data but still 16 deg deviation on toolface.

Slided 26" drilling BHA from 229 m to 249 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3100 lpm / SPP 68 bar / 8-10 MT WOB / Rotation 95 RPM (bit rpm)/ String torque 1-3 kNm. Pumped 10 m3 hi-vis sweep. Picked off bottom and hung off in slips.

Performed single shot survey on WL. Inclination 0,27 deg / Azimuth 334,1 deg / Toolface 076 deg. Secured drillstring using chain hoist at Centralizer deck. Pumped at 2000 lpm to obtain gMWD survey : Inclination 0,44 deg / Azimuth 024,1 deg / Toolface 076 deg - good match on toolface figure. Good match between realtime GTF and MTF.
Slided 26" drilling BHA from 249 m to 258 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3100 lpm / SPP 68 bar / 1-3 MT WOB / Rotation 95 RPM (bit rpm)/ String torque 0-2 kNm.
Drilled 26" hole section from 258 m to 269 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3100 lpm / SPP 68 bar / 1-3 MT WOB / Rotation 130 RPM (bit rpm) / String torque 6 kNm.

Drilled 26" hole section from 269 m to 530 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3100-4400 lpm / SPP 68-125 bar / WOB 2-8 MT / Torque 1-11 kNm / String RPM 40 / Bit RPM 40-170. Average ROP 15 m /hrs. Pumped 10 m3 hi-vis sweep for every singel drilled. Performed gMWD survey on connections. Secured drillstring with sling/chainhoist on Centralizer deck while performing survey.

Steered intervalls :
268 - 287 m MD
315 - 331 m MD
356 - 377 m MD
396 - 411 m MD
435 - 450 m MD
475 - 495 m MD
515 - 535 m MD

Drilled 26" hole section from 530 m to 636 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 4400 lpm / SPP 125-127 bar / WOB 6-8 MT / Torque 2-8 kNm / String RPM 40 / Bit RPM 40-170. Average ROP 18 m /hrs. Pumped 10 m3 hi-vis sweep for every singel drilled. Performed gMWD survey on connections. Secured drillstring with sling/chainhoist on Centralizer deck while performing survey.

Steered intervalls :
555 - 575 m MD
597 - 615 m MD

Drilled 26" section in rotation mode, from 636 m to 878 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 4400 - 4480 lpm / SPP 125 - 127 bar / WOB 6-10 MT / Torque 9 - 10 kNm / String RPM 40 / Bit RPM 165 - 172. Avarage ROP 20,3 m/ hrs.Pumped 10 m3 hi-vis sweep for every singel drilled.
Performed gMWD survey on connections.

Drilled 26" section in rotation mode, from 878 m to 981m MD. Reduced flow-rate from 4480 lpm to 4000 lpm due to Utsira sand. Hit top of utsira sand at 888 m. Drilling parameters : Flow 4000 lpm / SPP 121 bar / WOB 2 - 5 MT / Torque 3 - 5 kNm / String RPM 40 / Bit RPM 160- 162. Avarage ROP 38,1m/ hrs. Pumped 10 m3 hi- vis sweep for every singel drilled. Performed g MWD survey on connections

Drilled 26" section in rotation mode, from 981 m to  bottom of Utsira sand at 1064 m MD.  Drilling parameters : Flow 4000 lpm / SPP 121 bar / WOB 2 - 5 MT / Torque 3 - 5 kNm / String RPM 40 / Bit RPM 160- 162. Avarage ROP 41,5 m/ hrs. Pumped 10 m3 hi- vis sweep for every singel drilled. Performed g MWD survey on connections.

Drilled 26" hole from 1064 m to Td for section at 1083 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 4410 lpm / SPP 154 -156 bar / WOB 8 - 13 MT / Torque 10 -13 knm / String RPM 40 / Bit RPM 170. Avarage ROP 22,8 m/ hrs.Pumped 10 m3 hi.vis sweep for every singel drilled. Performed g MWD survey on connections.

At TD, pumped 30 m3 hi vis followed by 30 m3 sea watwr and then 55 m3 hi - vis. Reduced flow rate to 3500 lpm while pumping hi vis pill through BHA. Circulated hole clean with 4480 lpm / SPP 127-130 bar /String RPM 40 / Torque 3-4 kNm.  Kept bit below Utsira sand during circulation / reciprocation.

Displaced well to 1.40 sg bentonite mud with 3500 lpm / SPP 70 bar / String RPM 20 / Torque 1-4 kNm.  Kept bit below Utsira sand during displacment. SPP leveled out after 14500 strokes at 3500 lpm / SPP 152 bar /String RPM 180 / Torque 2-4 kNm. Observed some returns coming through cement ports on 30" conductor on F-4.

POOH with 26" drilling BHA from 1072 m MD to 717 m MD. Tight spots when POOH:

          807-800 m: 10-15 MT overpull
          770-764 m: 13-16 MT overpull
          758-754 m: 10-14 MT overpull
          725-720 m: 16-21 MT overpull

Encountered leak on PS21 slips.
Discovered leakage on PS 21 slips. Changed hose.

POOH with 26" drilling BHA from 717 m MD to 193 m MD. Tight spots when POOH:

          627-620 m: 2-10 MT overpull
          615-612 m: 5-15 MT overpull
          598-596 m: 11-20 MT overpull
          595-590 m: 10-30 MT overpull
          585-580 m: 15-30 MT overpull
          578-575 m: 5-15 MT overpull

Built scaffolding under centralizer deck on well head module.

Meanwhile topped up well with 1.40 sg mud at 193 m MD. Serviced TDS and PRS and performed derrick inspection for loose items.

Held tool box meeting before manual handling of BHA. Continued POOH with 26" drilling BHA from 193 m MD to OOH. ROV guided BHA out of template. Flushed string with SW when bit was above template. Clean and cleared rig floor of excess equipment.
LO pup joints on top of landing string. PU one joint HWDP. MU and RB cmt stand
Spotted csg handling equipment on rig floor.

Held pre-job meeting prior to handling DCI valve. Brought DCI frame down to scaffolding below centralizer deck through rotary and deck openings using tugger. Hung up and chained back DCI frame from well head centre using chain hoists and eagle clamps.
RU casing running equipment, 20 ft bails and FAC tool.
RU casing running equipment, 20 ft bails, elevators, csg tong, slips and FAC tool.
Held pre-job meeting prior to running 20" csg. PU 20" shoe joint. Encountered signal problems to casing tong.
Troubleshot ZMS signals on csg tong.
Continued PU 20" csg shoe assy. Encountered problems with FWD PRS & HTS
Troubleshoot signals and alignement on FWD PRS and HTS.
PU intermediate joint and float collar joint. Tread locked connections. Checked float in shoe and float collar for flow through with SW. Filled each joint with 90 strk SW.
RIH with 20" csg from 39 m to 109 m MD. Installed csg centralizers on each joint. Filled every joint with 90 strk SW. Average running speed 2 jnts/hr. Back-up chain on upper casing tong broke-off.
Back-up chains on upper part of casing tong broke off. Made up temporary solution with wire slings acting as back-up security to the counterbalance.

RIH with 20" csg from 109 m to 151 m MD. Installed one centralizer on each joint. Filled every joint with 90 strk SW. Average running speed 2 jnts/hr. 

Stabbed csg into conductor assisted by ROV. Had to use chain tongs in well head area to limit csg string movement in 3-4 m waves.

RIH with 20" csg from 151 m to 414 m MD. Filled string with SW every 5th joint. Average running speed 4 jnts/hr. 

Observed tight spots at:
250-256 m: 12 MT drag
282-293 m: 16 MT drag - circulated w/SW 650 lpm / 25 bar

RIH with 20" csg from 414 m to 923 m MD. Filled string with SW every 5th joint. Average running speed 5 jnts/hr. Upweight 188 MT/down weight 144 MT at last joint before WH housing.

Observed tight spots at:
576-588 m: 20-25 MT drag
701-738 m: 15-18 MT drag 
800-825 m: 12-15 MT drag
Greased slips prior to elevator change and topped-up casing with SW.
RD 20" csg handling equipment and RU 5 1/2" handling equipment.
PU 18 3/4" WH housing/CART assembly and MU to 20" casing. Oriented DCI valve outlet swivel to STB side using a ring bolt.
RIH with 18 3/4" WH housing/CART assembly from 923 m to 934 m. Removed PS30 slips and installed outer ring and master bushings.
RD csg tong and flush mounted elevators.
Continued RD csg tong and flush mounted elevators. Cleared rig floor.
RIH with 18 3/4" WH housing/CART assembly from 934 m to 953 m.  Observed 20 MT drag. Circulated with 450 lpm / 30 bar and washed down.
Removed gas sensor and section of grating on x-mas tree deck to enable safe passage of WH housing through deck. Continued RIH with 18 3/4" WH housing/CART assembly from 953 m to 965 m.
Held tool box talk prior to installing DCI valve. Installed DCI frame on 18 3/4" WH housing working on scaffolding platform below WH module.
Installed DCI frame on 18 3/4" WH housing working on scaffolding platform below WH module. Pressure tested DCI frame/ WH to 210 bar/ 5 min. Meanwhile held pre-job meeting for cement job.
Continued RIH with 20" casing on landing string from 965 m to 1065 m.  Washed down last 10 m 440 lpm / 38 bar. Upweight 188 MT/ down weight 138 MT.

Landed 18 3/4" WH into 30" conductor by setting down casing string weight + 5 MT to engage lock ring. Performed 25 MT overpull test. Slacked off and kept landing string in tension by an overpull of 3 MT.

Perfomed line test against HCR, 345 bar / 4 bar drop in 10 min. Attempted to re-test MS-seal. Observed volume mismatch and wrong line-up - bled off pressure.

Closed isolation valve on cement unit and monitored pressure on kill manifold from Gesoservice. Pressure Dropped from 329 to 320 bar in 30 min but no improvement observed. Discussed situation. Dedcided to work on valves and lines to obtain better line test before reverting to testing MS-seal.
Greased and operated valves on kill manifold and in moonpool. Changed valve #33 and #35 on cement unit. Greased valves on cement unit. Drained mud from cement unit and filled tanks with water.
Pressure tested cement unit against isolation valve. Obtained test to 345 bar with 1,3 bar drop / 10 min.

Tested kill line against valve in moonpool and K3 valve on kill manifold. Pressurized to 35 bar, dropped 0,5 bar / 5 min - ok. Pressurized to 345 bar, dropped 0,7 bar / 5 min - ok. 

Tested kill line against HCR valves. Pressurized to 35 bar, dropped 0,5 bar / 5 min - ok. Pressurized to 345 bar, dropped 1 bar / 5 min -ok.

Lined up to test MS-seal from above. Pressurized to 35 bar, dropped 0,6 bar 5 min - ok. Pressurized to 345 bar. Pressure dropped 0,7 bar / 5 min in the start but with gradually increasing fall off trend. Dropped 1,8 bar / 5 min towards the end of the test.  Pumped and bled back 373 liter. Bled off pressure and discussed situation. Decided to re-attempt pressurizing MS seal with PADPRT tool.

Re-sat PADPRT by applying 30 MT overpull. Pressurized to 207 bar to re-energize MS-seal. Held pressure for 10 min / 1,3 bar drop (0,5%). Slacked off overpull on PADPRT to relax bulk seal. Took 30 MT overpull to expose MS-seal.

Lined up to pressure test MS seal from above. Pressurized to 35 bar, pressure dropped 0,4 bar / 5 min - ok. Pressurized to 345 bar. Pressure dropped at 1,7 bar / 5 min in the beginning but improved towards the end of the test to 0,5 bar / 5 min. Last 10 min 1,1 bar drop (0,32%) - ok. Pumped and bled back 400 liter. Lost 20 MT on block while performing test.
Attempted to released PADPRT by slacking off weight and applying 4 rigihthand turns - nogo. Discussed situation.
Discussed way forward with regards to releasing PADPRT. Repeated PADPRT release procedure but got same negative result.
Awaited instructions for releasing PADPRT.

Reverted to emergency release procedure. Rotated string 13 times counterclockwise until torque bulid up of 10 000 Nm. Attempted to pull free with 40 MT overpull - nogo. Repeated emergency release procedure but got same negative result.
Awaited instructions for releasing PADPRT. Meeting ongoing with town.
Held toolbox talk for attempt to free PADPRT with straight pull release.
Stepped up hookload. Released PADPRT with 60 MT overpull. Observed 30 MT continuos drag after release.
Staged up pumps to 2650 lpm / SPP 25 bar. Circulated riser clean. Got fines over shakers.
Broke out and laid down cement head.
POOH with PADPRT on 5 1/2" HWDP fdrom 137 m MD to surface. Laid out PADPRT. Found tool cavities packed with cuttings.
Held toolbox talk prior to running wearbushing.
Made up jet sub and testable WBRRT.
RIH with jet sub / WBRRT on 5 1/2" DP from surface to 140 m MD. Washed across wellhead from 136,5 m to 143 m MD with 2650 lpm.
Set wearbushing at 140,5 m MD according to Vetco instructions. Applied 8 MT overpull to verify setting.
Lined up kill manifold for re-testing MS-seal. Closed UPR. Conducted line test against HCR to 345 bar / 5 min, dropped 0,6 bar - ok.

Attempted to replicate test on MS seal testing against WBRRT. Conducted low pressure test to 35 bar / 5 min - ok. Pressured up to 345 bar, not able to obtain good test, pressure leaked off at approx 3,5 bar / 10 min (~1%) and did not stabilize. Topped up drillpipe and observed for flow up drillpipe. Observed flow from drillpipe. Discussed situation. Decided to pull WBRRT and install test plug for test of MS-seal and BOP.
POOH with WBBRT from 140 m MD to surface. Laid down WBBRT.
Made up BOP test plug. RIH with BOP test plug on 5 1/2" DP from surface to 140 m MD.
Set plug in wearbushing according to Vetco instructions. Lined up for testing BOP and MS seal from cement unit.
Pressure tested BOP. Attempted to get test on MS-seal on BOP test #1 against LPR. Pressured up to 345 bar, leaked off at 2 bar / 10 min but did not stabilize.
Pressure tested BOP (test #2).
Pressure tested BOP, test #3 against UPR. Simultaneously pressure tested MS seal to 345 bar. Obtained test result of 1,3 bar / 10 min (0,37%) and improving trend - ok.
Pressure tested BOP (test #4 to #7).
Pressure tested BOP (test #7 and #8). Reverted to repair on TDS.
Parked TDS for service. Worked on TDS allignment cylinder. Meanwhile pressure tested valves in kill and choke manifolds to 35/345 bar 5/10 min.
Made up test swage to TDS and connected cement hose. Flushed and pressure tested line.
Pressure tested upper/lower IBOPs and kelly hose to 35/345 bar 5/10 min - ok.
Rigged down test swage and laid out same.
Continued working on TDS allignment cylinder.
POOH with BOP test plug on 5 1/2" DP from 140 m MD to surface.
Continued working on TDS allignment cylinder. Picked up single and installed in rotary for making final allignment on TDS.
Held toolbox talk prior to picking up 12 1/4" drilling BHA.
Picked up 12 1/4" powerdrive xceed and hung off in rotrary. Gauged bit. Picked up and made up xceed/motor and made up same.
Picked up C-link assy. Not able to spin in threads. Tendencies of thread gaulling in box. Washed threads. Refurbished and grinded threads as required.
Reinstalled lift sub on C-link assy to check threads - ok. Made up schlumberger C-link assy - ok.

Picked up and made up ARC, Powerpulse, Sonicvison, NMDC and NMDC pony. 

Meanwhile lined up for testing CRI hose and perform injection test. Observed that CRI hose had detached from subsea wellhead. Valve on hose and check valve was dug in the mud/seabed. Attempted to grab valve assembly but could not apply enough force with ROV.

Made up stand og 8 1/4" DC and jar. Made up stand of DC. Made up x-over. Picked up and made up 4 x 5 1/2" HWDP singles (1 stand).

Meanwhile deployed moonpool tugger to assist ROV in recovering CRI valve assembly from mud/seabed.
Held toolbox talk. Removed masterbushing and installed automatic slips in rotary

RIH with 12 1/4" drilling BHA on 5 1/2" DP from 159 m to 526 m MD.

Meanwhile worked to recover CRI valve assembly with ROV and tugger assist. Closed valve on subsea wellhead.
Made up TDS. Circulated according to Schlumberger instructions and performed shallow test of MWD.
RIH with 12 1/4" drilling BHA on 5 1/2" DP from 526 m to 2139 m MD. Broke circulation every 500 m.
Checked allignement of TDS.
Held handover meeting and toolbox meeting prior to chokedrill. Performed choke drill.
Continued to RIH with 12 1/4" BHA on 5 1/2" DP from 2139 m to 2206.
Laid out single from stand #51 to space out for drilling shoetrack and rathole without connection.
Made up TDS and broke circulation. Whashed down from 2206 m at 2650 lpm / SPP 123 bar and tagged cement plug at 2247,8 m MD.
Drilled on cement plugs at 2248 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 2700 lpm / SPP ~120 bar / String RPM 105 / WOB 3-6 MT / Torque ~5 kNm / ECD 1,31-1,32. Picked off bottom every 10-15 min to clean bit.
Broke through plugs/float collar. Drilled firm cement from 2248 m to shoe at 2275 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 2700 lpm / SPP ~120 bar / String RPM 105 / WOB 1-3 MT / Torque 5-9 kNm / ECD 1,32.

Cleaned rathole below 14" casing down to 2281 m MD.  Remaed through shoe for every 2 m drilled. Drilling parameters : Flow 2500-3000 lpm / SPP 113-140 bar / String RPM 105-115 / WOB 1-2 MT / Torque ~7 kNm / ECD 1,32.
Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2281 m to 2284 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 2500-3000 lpm / SPP 114-145 bar / String RPM 105-115 / WOB 3-4 MT / Torque 7-9 kNm / ECD 1,32.

Circulated at 3000 lpm to clean hole and get even mudweight. Observed clean shakers and even MW in/out of 1,30 sg. Meanwhile made preparations for XLOT. Transferred mud to cementer and flushed kill line to drillfloor. Set choke on cement unit bleed back. Pulled bit inside casing.
Closed UPR. Verifed line up to standpipe 1 and kill line to BOP.
Performed XLOT cycle #1. Pressured up on well to ~100 bar at 92 lpm. observed fall off trend for 15 min. Pumped 1776 l and bled back 775 l.
Performed XLOT cycle #2. Pressured up on well to ~98 bar at 92 lpm. Observed fall off trend for 15 min.
Bled back after XLOT cycle #2. Pumped 1770 l and bled back 1150 l. Observed pressure bulid up for 15 min after bleed off. Meanwhile had toolbox talk prior to mud displacement.

Lined up for mud displacement. Pumped 8 m3 WBM spacer and 10 m3 hv-vis OBM spacer. Tripped in to TD at 2284 m MD. Pumped 200 m3 og 1,30 sg OBM at 3000 lpm / SPP 170 bar. Decreased pump rate to 1000 lpm / SPP 25 bar towards end of displacement. Took WBM back to pits and separated treatable and non-treatable interface.
Established closed circulation system. Opened for shakers. Filled poor-boy and sand traps. Filled trip tanks.
Racked back 1 stand. Picked up single and made up to stand #51.

RIH to 2280 m MD and attempted to establish drilling parameters. Pumped at 3000 lpm but got overflow on shakers. Cut back rate to 1700 lpm to be able to handle flow. Stepped up rate to 3000 lpm as dictated by flow on shakers.

Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2284 m to 2289 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3500 lpm / SPP 232 bar / String RPM 44 / Bit RPM 144/ WOB 2-3 MT / Torque 7-8 kNm / ECD 1,32 / ROP 20 m/hr. Experienced problems with MWD signal.
Trouble-shoot MWD signal. Meanwhile drilled ahead 1 m of 12 1/4" hole.

Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2290 m to 2299 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3500 lpm / SPP 232 bar / String RPM 44 /  Bit RPM 144 / WOB 2-3 MT / Torque 7-8 kNm / ECD 1,32 / ROP 20 m/hr. Experienced problems with FWD PRS.
Re-booted software on FWD PRS. Meanwhile circulated with 3000 lpm / 10 rpm and reamed up/down 20 m.

Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2299 m to 2460 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3500 lpm / SPP 232-238 bar / String RPM 120-140 / Bit RPM 220-240 / WOB 3-8 MT / Torque 6-13 kNm / ECD 1,32 /  Drilled with limited ROP 20-30 m/hr due to problems with MWD sinal decoding.

Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2460 m to 2591 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3500 lpm / SPP 238-249 bar / String RPM 140 / Bit RPM 240 / WOB 3-8 MT / Torque 6-13 kNm / ECD 1,32-1,33 /  ROP 30-50 m/hr. Hard stringers encountered at 2518-2519 m and 2565-2568 m MD.

Meanwhile inspected CRI hose using ROV.
Used 4 attempts to downlink to Schlumberger powerdrive. Meanwhile drilled ahead with limited ROP from 2591 m to 2593 m.

Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2593 m to 2638 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3500 lpm / SPP 249 bar / String RPM 140 / Bit RPM 240 / WOB 6-11 MT / Torque 13-18 kNm / ECD 1,32-1,33 /  ROP 40-50 m/hr in Ty formation and 10-25 m/hr in Ekofisk formation.
Used 5 attempts to downlink to Schlumberger powerdrive. Meanwhile drilled ahead with limited ROP from 2638 m to 2648 m. Performed downlink with bit off botm.

Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2648 m to 2666 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3500 lpm / SPP 240-246 bar / String RPM 140 / Bit RPM 240 / WOB 11 MT / Torque 14-16 kNm / ECD 1,32 /  ROP 10-15 m/hr in Ekofisk formation. Up weight 168 mT / Down weight 150 mT / Rotating weight 157 mT.

Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2666 m to 2704 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3100 lpm / SPP 233-235 bar / String RPM 140 / Bit RPM 240 / WOB 11 MT / Torque 13-14 kNm / ECD 1,32 /  ROP 9-10 m/hr in Ekofisk formation. Up weight 171 mT / Down weight 147 mT / Rotating weight 157 mT.
Used 4 attempts to downlink to Schlumberger powerdrive. Meanwhile drilled ahead with limited ROP from 2704 m to 2713 m.

Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2713 m to 2754 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3500 lpm / SPP 250 bar / String RPM 155 / Bit RPM 255 / WOB 11-12 MT / Torque 19-25 kNm / ECD 1,33-1,34 /  ROP 35-40 m/hr
Used several attempts to downlink to Schlumberger powerdrive. Meanwhile drilled ahead with limited ROP from 2754 m to 2772 m.

Drilled 12 1/4" hole section from 2772 m to 2788 m MD. Drilling parameters : Flow 3200 lpm / SPP 225 bar / String RPM 155 / Bit RPM 255 / WOB 11 MT / Torque 15-35 kNm / ECD 1,33-1,34 /  ROP 50 m/hr. Up weight 175 mT / down weight 147 mT / rotating weight 158 mT.
Performed final downlink and took final survey. RB one std.

Circulated well clean while reciprocated drill string. Pumped 4 x BU at: Flow 3300 lpm / SPP 124 bar / Upwards RPM 40 / Downwards RPM 120.

Meanwhile MU and checked gyro tools on main deck. PU and MU gyro tool on drill floor.
Installed battery and dropped gyro tool string inside DP. Pumped down tool with 500-660 lpm and landed gyro on totco ring at 2659,9 m. Performed rotational shots and gyro tool QC at 2655,9 m.

Flow checked well for 15 min. Ok. POOH 5 stds wet from 2785 m to 2583 m. Flow checked well. Ok. Pumped 5 m3 slug. 

Meanwhile performed gyro survey on connection while POOH.

Continued POOH with 12 1/4" BHA from 2583 m and into 14" csg shoe at 2259. Flow checked well for 15 min. Ok.

Meanwhile performed gyro survey on connection while POOH.

POOH with 12 1/4" BHA from 2259 m to 133 m.

Meanwhile performed gyro survey on connection while POOH.

BO stand to pick out gyro string. Found gyro tool to be 1 m below connection. MU dedicated fishing tool on tugger and removed tool string out of HWDP. Managed to get gyro data from 2655,9 m to mudline.

Meanwhile flow checked well. Ok.
RB and LD 12 1/4" BHA from 133 m to 88 m.
RB and LD 12 1/4" BHA from 88 m to OOH. Cleaned and cleared rig floor.
Held tool box talk with involved personnel. MU and RIH with jet sub and wear bushing retrieving tool from surface to 138 m.
Jetted area from 138 m to 142 m. Released wear bushing and POOH. LO WBRT assembly and jet sub.
Cleaned and cleared rig floor prior to rigging up for csg equipment.
Serviced TDS and inspected derrick and top drive for loose items after drilling 12 1/4" section.
RU 9 5/8" csg running equipment.
Held time out for safety with both crews.
Continue RU 9 5/8" csg running equipment.
Held pre job meeting for running csg with focuse on red zone policy. Built scaffolding shelter for csg tong operator on drillfloor.
PU shoe joint.
PU and MU intermediate- and float collar joint. Threads locked connections and checked integrity of shoe and float when RIH.
RIH with 9 5/8" XO from Vam Top to Vam Top HC. Adjusted roller guides on csg tong.
RIH with 9 5/8" Vam Top HC csg w/centr from 49 m to 272 m. Filled csg using top drive every joint. Tripping speed was 6-8 joints/hr. Had hydraulic oil leak on iron roughneck.
Repaired bursted fitting on iron roughneck.
RIH with 9 5/8" Vam Top HC csg w/centr from 272 m to 339 m. Filled csg using top drive every joint. Tripping speed was 9 joints/hr.
RIH with 9 5/8" Vam Top HC csg w/centr from 339 m to 490 m. Filled csg using top drive every joint. Tripping speed was 4-7 joints/hr. Coupling leaking on Odfjell casing tong.
Changed leaking coupling on Odfjell csg tong.
LO jnt #358 due to damaged box.
RIH with 9 5/8" Vam Top HC csg from 490 m to 1170 m. Crossed over from Vam Top HC to Vam Top at 753.6 m. Filled csg using top drive every joint. Tripping speed was 6-11 joints/hr.
Held pre-job meeting. Changed to 10 3/4" handling equipment and RU casing circulation tool (FAC). Experienced problems with Odfjell spider elevator.
Sorted out problem with Odfjell spider elevator.
PU and installed XO 9 5/8" x 10 3/4". Changed out PS21 slips with PS30 slips. Problems with PDM camera.
Repaired camera on PDM and re-sat HMI software to be able to see picture on the screen.
RIH with 10 3/4" csg from 1188 m to 1218 m.  Filled csg using FAC tool every joint. Tripping speed was 4 jnts/hr.
RIH with 10 3/4" csg from 1218 m to 1763 m.  Filled csg using FAC tool every joint. Topped up every 5 joints. Tripping speed was 7-11 jnts/hr.

RIH with 10 3/4" csg from 1763 m to 2640 m.  Filled csg using FAC tool every joint. Topped up every 5 joints. Tripping speed was 5-11 jnts/hr. Broke circulation at shoe with 2200 lpm / 27 bar and circulated 15 min at 1700 lpm / 31 bar.
Held tool box meeting and RD FAC tool and changed bails. Changed to 5 1/2" HWDP handling equipment.

PU and MU 10 3/4" casing hanger / PADPRT assembly. Marked running tool to make sure it was not backing out. Took out master bushing and ran hanger assy through rotary. Re-installed master bushing. Removed csg tong.
RIH with 10 3/4" x 9 5/8" csg on 5 1/2" HWDP landing string from 2640 to 2779 m MD.
Ball dropped out when PU cement head. Reloaded ball and MU cmt head. Lined up and pressure tested cmt line 345 bar / 5 min.
Established circulation at 1500 lpm / 42 bar and washed down from 2779 m to 2783 m. Landed off 10 3/4" x 9 5/8" csg at 140.5 m and sat down 5 ton. Kept 5 ton on landing string.
Circulated casing volume and btms up, a total of 1150 strks, at 1770 lpm / 53 bar loss free rate. Observed 3 m3/hr loss at 2000 lpm but had full return at 1770 lpm.
Continued circulating casing volume and btms up at 1770 lpm / 53 bar loss free rate. Meanwhile held pre-job meeting for cmt job.
Pumped 30 m3 contaminated OBM, 5 m3 base oil and 19 m3 spacer at 1550-1770 lpm / 46-53 bar.
Verified correct line-up by holding and releasing 20 bar through low torque. Mixed and pumped 13,7 m3 1.90 sg cement slurry at 800 lpm / 31 bar.

Pumped 500 ltrs water, released dart and continued pumping 2500 ltrs water behind cement with cmt unit. Top wiper plug sheared at 170 bar. 

Zeroed stroke counters for mud pumps. Displaced and sheared btm wiper plug by pumping OBM at 1200 lpm using rig pumps. 
Continued displacing cement with 111.9 m3 OBM at 1770-1500 lpm using mud pumps. Wiper plug sheared at 114 bar / 4450 stks. Slowed down rate to 1000 lpm / 69 bar (FCP) approx 4 m3 prior to bump. Bumped plug with 138 bar after pumping 5080 strokes, which gives a pump efficiency of 96.5%. No losses during displacement.

Equalized pressure with cmt unit and opened lo-torque valve. Pressured up well to 345 bar / 15 min to test casing using cmt unit. Ok. 1250 ltrs pumped and got 1220 ltrs back. Bleed off from 345 bar to 138 bar and checked for back flow to cmt unit. Lined over to rig pumps and bled off from 138 bar to zero on stand pipe. Checked for back flow. Disconnected cmt hoses and flushed lines.
Reduced weight on landing string from 5 mT to neutral and released PADPRT. LD cmt head std. Dropped sponge balls and flushed string using mud. POOH and LD PADPRT.

PU and RIH with lock down sub from surface to 140 m. Landed lock down sub and made 4 1/4 turns CW, torque 1700 Nm with neutral weight. Toolstring dropped 7.7 inches. Attempted to to set lock down sub. No go.

1) Performed line test from cmt unit to HCR valve, 30/220 bar 5/10 min. Ok.
2) Pressured up to set lock down sub against closed top pipe ram. No go.
3) Checked for possible leaks in toolstring by opening IBOP and monitor gain in trip tank. No leak observed.
4) Pressured up to set lock down sub against closed btm pipe ram. No go.
5) Pulled lock down sub 1 m above landing no go. Flushed wellhead with 1100 lpm / 15 min.  Landed lock down sub and made 4 1/4 turns CW, torque 1700 Nm with neutral weight. Toolstring dropped 8 inches. Attempted to set lock down sub. No go.
POOH with lock down sub assembly from 140 m to OOH. Checked lock down sub and verified space out. Ok. LD lock down sub.
PU and RIH with jet/flush tool from surface to 140 m. Landed out on 140.03 m.
Jetted top of 10 3/4" csg hanger, 750 lpm / 42 bar / 3 rpm / 2 kNm.
POOH with jet/flush tool from 140 m to OOH. Inspected jetting tool and found indication that tool had not landed out on 10 3/4" csg hanger.
RIH with jet/flush tool from surface to 140 m.

Landed out with jet/flush tool on 10 3/4" csg hanger with 2 mT. PU and established circulation at 910 lpm / 49 bar / 3 rpm / 2 kNm. Tagged with 2 mT serveral times to clean the CH area. PU 1 m and circulated btms up at 930 lpm / 45 bar.
POOH with jet/flush tool from 139 m to 100 m.
POOH with jet/flush tool from 100 m to 60 m. Could not rack back 5 1/2" HWDP due to finger on FWD PRS not working.
Repaired decoder for finger on FWD PRS.

POOH with jet/flush tool from 600 m to OOH. Inspected jetting tool and found indication that tool had not landed out completely on 10 3/4" csg hanger. Decided that it was no point in re-running the jet/wash tool.
PU and RIH with lock down sub from surface to 40 m. Could not rack back 5 1/2" HWDP due to finger on fingerboard not working.

Repaired decoder for finger on FWD PRS.

Meanwhile changed out drilling bails and performed derrick inspection.
RIH with lock down sub from 40 to 140 m.

Landed lock down sub with 9 mT and made 4 1/4 turns CW, torque 1700 Nm with neutral weight. Toolstring dropped 7.5 inches. Closed UPR and verified correct line-up. 
Attempted to pressure up to 35 bar without sucess. Switched to second cmt pump and re-tried pumping up to 35 bar. Ok. Continued pressuring up to 207 bar and sat MS seal. Bled off pressure to zero. Confirmed lock by taking 40 mT overpull.
Tested MS in lock down sub 35/345 bar for 5/10 min. Ok
Released PADPRT and POOH with running string from 140 m to OOH.
Held tool box meeting prior to running RTTS. MU and RIH with jet sub from surface to 30 m and jetted BOP, 3100 lpm / 22 bar / 10 rpm.
Continue RIH with jet sub on 4 stds of 5 1/2" HWDP from 30 m to 87 m. PU and MU RTTS w/storm valve. Ran Halliburton centrilizer on single above storm valve.
RIH with 10 3/4" RTTS w/SSCV on 5 1/2" DP from 87 m to 350 m. Up weight 92 mT / down weight 97 mT.
Reciprocated string and circulated at 290 lpm / 7 bar to clean setting area. Installed RTTS with elements at 350 m and sat down 20 mT, down weight 70 mT.

Lined up to test RTTS from below. Verified correct line-up from cmt unit to IBOP and performed line test. No go. Closed manual IBOP on TDS and performed line test. Ok. 

Performed low pressure test to 30 bar / 10 min. Ok. Dropped 1 bar / 10 min. Pressured up in steps and tested RTTS to 230 bar / 10 min from below. Ok. Dropped 1.8 bar / 10 min. 1.3 m3 pumped and 1.35 m3 bled back.
PU up to neutral and released from RTTS with 22 turns CCWW. PU to 340 m.
Pulled up and greased top of connection. Ran back down to and spaced out below btm pipe ram.

Lined up cmt unit to IBOP on TDS to test RTTS from above and performed line test to 345 bar. Ok.

Performed low pressure test to 30 bar / 10 min. Ok. Dropped 0 bar / 10 min. Pressured up in steps to test RTTS. Pumped 1.1 m3 to 110 bar and observed leak. 500 ltrs bleed back.
Discussed situation and evaluated further action.
Discussed situation and evaluated further action.

Stung back into RTTS. Observed 2.2 bar pressure increase when communication to volume below plug was established. 

Lined up to test RTTS from below. Closed manual IBOP on TDS. Performed low pressure test to 30 bar / 10 min. Ok. Dropped 0 bar / 10 min. Pressured up in steps and tested RTTS to 230 bar / 10 min from below. Ok. Dropped 1.7 bar / 10 min. 1.33 m3 pumped and 1.32 m3 bled back.

Rotated 12 turns to the left and POOH of RTTS. Tested storm valve to 50 bar / 10 min. Ok. Dropped 0.9 bar / 10 min.  121 ltrs pumped and 121 ltrs bled back. Stung out of RTTS.

Flow checked well prior to displacing well above RTTS to SW. Ok. Meanwhile held tool box talk with involved personnel. Drained trip tank and poor boy degasser. Re-filled trip tank with SW. Displaced well to SW at 3100 lpm / 20 bar. Flushed C & K and surface lines.
Pumped 10 m3 hi-vis pill at 1500 lpm / 15 bar and spotted above RTTS.
POOH with running tool on 5 1/2" DP from 348 m to 310 m. Could not rack back 5 1/2" DP due spinner on iron roughneck not working.
Investigated problem with pipe spinner on aft roughneck.
Held tool box meeting prior to using chain tong to spin out stds of DP.

Observed gain in trip tank and flow up RTTS running string. Installed kick valve on string. Shut in well and monitored pressures. No increase in pressure observed. Total gain in trip tank was 420 ltrs.

Opened auto choke and observed no gain in TT through mud gas separator. Opened kick valve and observed no flow. POOH with running tool on 5 1/2" DP from 310 m to 292 m. Could not rack back 5 1/2" DP due to lower arm on FWD PRS not working.

Changed out solenoid valve on lower arm on FWD PRS.

Meanwhile removed every second bolt on slick joint and moved BOP carrier beneath BOP.
Held tool box talk for manual handling. Performed equipment check and found loose dies on FWD PRS carrier. Changed dies.
POOH with running tool on 5 1/2" DP from 292 m to OOH.
Cleared rig floor. RIH with 1 single 5 1/2" DP and closed ram. Drained BOP.
Installed diverter pulling tool.
Continued installing diverter pulling tool and POOH with diverter.
LO diverter.
Continued LO diverter.
RU for pulling slick joint. Pulled master bushing. Pulled and LO slick joint.
Removed tension cylinders from BOP.

Removed slings from TDS. PU claxton tool using BX-elevator and ran Claxton tool through rotary. Installed master bushings and 5 1/2" DP slips.

Meanwhile unbolted NT2 connector on BOP.
Helt tool box meeting. Moved BOP to stump. MU NT2 connector to stump and adjusted scaffolding according to Vetco request.
Held tool box meeting. MU Claxton tool to 5 1/2" DP and installed NT2 connector on to HPDR.

Held tool box meeting before removing tension cylinders. Transfered weight from riser tension system to TDS. PU up to 130 mT. Dismantled tensioner ring system.

Meanwhile dismantled annular and cleaned lines from cmt unit through kill, choke and poorboy degasser. Installed cradle and trolly on HTS.

Removed moonpool hatch on F-14 and hatch on F-13 for guide wire. Ran 10 mT tugger to moonpool. Production shut down confirmed at 23:55.

Meanwhile function tested riser spider.

Slacked off weight from 129 mT to 110 mT to have TBC in neutral. Installed guide wire using 10 mT tugger. Launched hotstab on mini-reel hose down to seabed, attached to guidewire. Removed dummy hot stab and installed hydraulic hot stab into receptacle at top of TBC using ROV.
Operated TBC valve panel to "Primary unlock" 2-1-1 using ROV and pressured up through mini-reel to 3000 psi. Held pressure for 15 min and confirmed position of indicator rods and unlock band.
Pulled riser 1.5 m above WH using 10-20 mT overpull. Disconnected hot stab and retrieved same.
POOH with riser until connection for 5 1/2" DP was above rotary. Disconnected 5 1/2" DP from Claxton tool and RB same. MU and RB RT for production riser.

PU riser and removed master bushings and ring.  Positioned split spider and installed same.

Parked IR. Installed and hooked up Odfjell tubing running tong.

Made up tubing hanger landing string comprising of 1 x 12 m 7" tubing, 1 x 6 m 7" tubing, 1 x 1 m 7" tubing, THRT, Swadge with FOSV's and side entry. Used single joint elevator to pick up tubing. Observed damage on pin end of 7" tubing joint in landing string. Observed damage on rig floor tugger wire.
Checked rig floor tugger for damaged and respooled same.
Laid out damaged tubing joint (#240) in landing string. Picked up and made up new 7" tubing joint (#196).
Made up THRT and racked back TH landing string in derrick. Continued rigging tubing running equipment.
Cleared and tidied drillfloor prior to bringing in control line reels.
Held toolbox talk with rig and completion crews.
Spotted WD and BOT control line reels on stb fwd setback. Suspened control line sheave in fwd PRS using PRS lifting tool. Dressed BX elevator with 7" inserts. Dressed slips and dogcollars.
Held toolbox talk with rig and completion crews.

Picked up of and hung off assy#1 Ratcheting muleshoe / stinger. Picked up and made up assy#2 - 9 5/8" Granite packer. Picked up and made up assy#3- 20" completion PBR. Made up and ran 3 x 7" tubing joint.
Picked up and made up assy#4 DHPG/CIV. Made up joint on top of completion assy#4 to ease termination of controlines.
Held toolbox talk prior to terminating DHPG/CIV completion assemblies.
Stripped and splitted control line. Terminated DHPG cable according to WD procedure. Tested conductivity - ok. Tested cable fitting to 10.000 psi through test port - ok.

RIH with tubing to place in working height for terminatining CIV control line. Stripped and bevelled control line. Installed CIV in carrier. Tested control line termination fitting to 10.000 psi through test port - ok. Tried to obtain ~50 bar on control line, hydraulic pump not suited for supplying low pressure (spiked when pressuring up).  Pressure up several time to obtain stable pressue. Hard to determine if there was a leakage on fitting closest to the carrier.
Cleaned and air blasted check valve assembly and fittings to check for leaks. Observed no leaks - control line pressure steady on 25 bar - ok.

Made up 7" tubing joint (#234). High and erratic thread torque. Backed out connection, cleaned threads and observed gaulling. Laid out joint #234. Refreshed box on joint #235. Picked up and made up next tubing joint - ok.
Removed masterbushing. Installed and hooked up FMS. Had problems with HTS tailing arm.
Troublehshot HTS tailing arm.
Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 100 m to 240 MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar.
Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 240 m to 300 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar.
Held toolbox/handover meeting. Checked and greased equipment.
Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 300 m to 785 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Average running speed 54 m/hrs.

Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 785 m to 842 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Tested combination of tubing tong die inserts with regards to marks/damage on tubing. Decided to run with standard die inserts below GLV. Average running speed 13 m /hrs (due to die trials),
Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 842 m to 1081 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Average running speed 60 m/hrs.
Troubleshot HTS tailing arm.
Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 1081 m to 1177 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Average running speed 77 m/hrs.
Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 1177 m to 1249 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Average running speed 72 m/hrs.

Picked up and made up assy#4 Schlumberger gas lift mandrel. Counted joints left on deck - 138 - ok. Removed FMS and installed masterbushing for using manual slips. Made up tubing joint on top og assy#4 to ease bypassing with control line. Stripped control line mantle. Installed clamps and inserts across GLV slot. Installed extra clamp on #assy4 upper pup joint due to bend on controll line. Removed masterbushing and installed FMS. Dressed tong with low marking dies.
Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 1269 m to 1400 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Got problems with HTS conveyer belt. Average running speed 75 m/hrs.
Troubleshot problem with conveyer belt. Meanwhile greased slips and elevator.
Troubleshot HTS. Found burned power distribution circuit. Made repair as required.
Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 1400 m to 1565 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Average running speed 73 m/hrs. Observed leakage from BX elevator.
Changed damaged hose on BX-elevator.
Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 1565 m to 1732 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Average running speed 55 m/hrs.

Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 1732 m to 1851 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Reduced running speed due to increasig drag ~5 MT in well when completion assemblies enetered 9 5/8" casing. Average running speed 43 m/hrs.
Ran 7" 29# S13%Cr110 tubing from 1851 m to 2100 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Average running speed 66 m/hrs.
Held toolbox talk prior to lifting in assy#6 FLX/ASV. Counted joints left on deck - 67 - ok.
Removed FMS and installed masterbushing. Lifted assy#6 FLX/ASV onto HTS. Lifted in assy#6 with elevator and drillfloor tugger and made up same.

Took measurements. Cut, stripped and splitted control line. Dressed DHPG control line ends. Installed and made up splice cylinder according to WD procedure. Installed lower connector on chemical injection line.

Tested fittings on DHPG lower spilce fitting through dedicated test port 10 min / 10000 psi - ok. Got problem with chart recorder. Continued testing by visual observation. Tested upper DHPG splice fitting 10 min / 10000 psi - ok.

Tested fitting on chemical injection line lower connector 10 min / 10000 psi - ok. Installed upper conncetor on chemical injection line. Mated chemical injection line connectors. Tested upper fitting on chemical injection line 10 min / 10000 psi - ok.  Meanwhile lowered sheave suspended in PRS due to hydraulic leak from PRS.

Installed connector protection clamp and adjusted same. Picked up and took in slack on control line by adjusting standard clamp below. Rigged up sheave for DHSV/ASV control line. Blinded off redundant hydraulic line from FLX/ASV and secured same in connector protection clamp. Ran  FLX/ASV through RT and checked same according to BOT procedure.
Made up 7" tubing joint to assy#6. Cut and dressed control lines for splicing.

Dressed dual control line for ASV/DHSV and fed through sheave. Made up ASV control line according to BOT procedure. Tested ASV control line to 570 bar / 10 min - ok. Tested redundant control line to 345 bar / 10 min - ok. Installed blind fitting on redundant line.
Flushed chemcial injection line and confirmed correct line up. Installed chemical injection lower connector and tested fitting to 10000 psi / 10 min - ok.
Spliced DHPG control line above FLX/ASV according to WD procedure. Tested conductivity - ok.
Pressure tested uppr/lower fitting on DHPG splice to 10000 psi / 10 min -ok. Connected chemical injection line and tested fitting on upper connector to 10000 psi / 10 min - ok.
Installed protectors/clamps and adjusted to take slack on control lines.
Function tested ASV according to BOT procedure - ok.
Picked and made up assy#7 DHSV. Picked up 7" joint (#62) and made up same to ease installation of control line and protectors/clamps.
Installed and fitted control line special clamps accross DHSV. Flushed DHSV control line and made up same to DHSV according to BOT procedure. Tested DHSV contrrol line to 570 bar / 10 min - ok.
Removed master bushing and installed FMS in rotary. Ran 1 joint of tubing.
Perfomed toolbox talk / handover meeting (new Mærsk drilling crew).
Ran 7" 29# S13%cr110 tubing from 2156 m MD to 2498 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Average running speed 76 m/hrs.
Ran 7" 29# S13%cr110 tubing from 2498 m MD to 2596 m MD. Installed control line clamp/protector on every collar. Average running speed 65 m/hrs.

Changed insert in BX elevator to 5 1/2". Counted joints on deck - 27 - ok. Picked up landing stand with 7" swadge. Installed control line clamp. Made up landing stand to completion string. Made up TDS. RIH with completion on 5 1/2" landing stand. Started pumping at 200 lpm when passing 2610 m MD. Tagged with ~5 MT at 2615,4 m MD without observing pressure build up. Picked up ~2 m to index ratcheting muleshoe and tried to enter PBR twice more - nogo. Picked up 3-4 m, ran in and entered PBR on 4th attempt. Observed pressure bulid up and reduced fluid returns when entering PBR, shut down pump. Tagged top of PBR with end of string at 2620 m MD.
Pulled out with landing stand. Broke out landing stand and racked back same. Changed inserts in BX elvevator to 7". Meanwhile performed space out calculation.
Laid out joint #16 and replaced with joint #21 to put stinger no-go 0,35 m above PBR. Prepared for picking up tubing hanger.
Picked up and made up 13 5/8" TH with handling tool. Cut, stripped and prepared control lines for pulling through TH.
Installed fittings on control lines and pulled control lines through TH. Made up fittings on control lines on bottom/top of TH. Unable to get good test on TH penetration fittings.

Found leakage across fittings for DHSV. Made several attempts to fix fitting with locktite - negative. Took out DHSV control line. Removed fittings and installed new ones. Applied lock tite to fitting threads.
Allowed locktite thread compound to harden prior to pressure test.
Pressure tested TH fittings to 35 / 345 bar 5 / 10 min - ok.
Installed C-plate. Landed TH in C-plate.
Broke off TH handling tool and laid down same.
Wrapped control lines around tubing hanger neck. Installed communication collar and teminated 3 ea hydraulic lines in same. Changed to 5 1/2" inserts in BX elevator.

Picked up TH landing stand. Made up THRT to TH with 9 counterclockwise turns using chain tongs. Made up control lines for chemical injection, ASV and DHSV to THRT. Pressure tested DHSV/ASV control lines. Made up control lines for THRT activation.

Removed C-plate and masterbushing. Ran TH/THRT through rotary. Installed masterbushing. Positioned stinger at 2613 m MD approx 3 m above PBR at 2615,4 m. Made up cement hose to side entry on landing string. Marked tubing with TH landing point.
Lined up for pumping baseoil down tubing taking returns to pits. Checked out alarm on mud pump liner spray.
Pumped baseoil in to tubing at 200 lpm to obtain underbalance in well.
Pumped baseoil in to tubing at 200 lpm to obtain underbalance in well. Pressure increased from 0,5 bar to 6,9 bar during displacement. Pumped a total of 10 m3. Took up/down weight 170/150 MT.

Ran in and attempted to land TH in wellhead. Unable to enter PBR at 2615,4 m MD. Picked up and attempted several (12) times to enter PBR - negative. Set down max 7 MT. At last attempt, observed that string moved incrementallly (2-3 cm) for each time weight was set down. Discussed situation - meanwhile maintained ~5 MT downweight. Observed sudden drop in applied weight - stinger free to move downwards. Drained riser. Landed tubing hanger at correct datum mark. Observed pressure buliding up from 6 bar to 11 bar indicating sealstem travel.

Tested tubing hanger through port#1 and #2 in multibowl, 35 bar / 5 min - ok. Pressured up TH function line to enagage tubing hanger lock ring. Performed overpull test to 185 MT, i.e. 15 MT above last upweight. Lined up cement unit and performed line test against closed lo-torque valve on landing stand, 345 bar / 5 min - ok.
Pressure tested tubing/sealstem to 50 bar / 5 min - ok. Volume pumped 149 liter.
Closed DHSV and bled off pressure above to ~3 bar. Bled back 30 liter. Held inflow test for 10 min - ok. Equalized across DHSV and opened same. Volume pumped 50 liter.

Pressured up to 345 bar at 120 lpm to set production packer and test tubing. Held test for 25 min - improving trend last 15 min (5 min 1,3 bar => 5 min 0,7 bar => 5 min 0,5 bar) - ok. Pumped a total of 1088 liter. Packer installed at 2598 mMDRT.

Bled down tubing pressure to 280 bar, bled back volume 180 liter. Closed DHSV and bled off pressure above to 156 bar, bled back volume 90 liter. Not able to adjust the choke to the intended 210 bar. Inflow tested DHSV to 125 bar differential. Held test for 15 min - increased 0,2 bar last 5 min with improving trend - ok.

Bled down tubing pressure from 156 bar to 10 bar to put 270 bar differential across the DHSV. Bled back 100 liter. Held inflow test for 30 min - test improving by time, last 5 min 0,02 bar increase. Equalised pressure (280 bar) accross DHSV and opened same. Pumped 190 liter. Bled back pressure on tubing to line up for pressure testing annulus. Total bled back volume 940 liter.
Lined up to maintain pressure on string while pressuring up tubng x casing annulus. Rigged down kill hose from F-12 and attached to hose on F-14 A-annulus. Pressured up to 100 bar on tubing.
Lined up cement unit and performed line test against closed lo-torque on A-annulus, 35/345 bar 5/10 min - ok.

Pressured up to 330 bar on A-annulus to set FLX packer and test production packer from above. maintained pressrue on tubing >100 bar. Held pressure for 15 min / 0,2 bar drop - ok. Total volume pumped 1107 liter. Vented B-annulus while performing test.

Bled down pressure on A-annulus to 270 bar, bled back 60 liters. Closed ASV and bled off pressure above to 200 bar to put 70 bar differential across ASV, bled back 160 liters. Inflow tested ASV for 15 mins - ok.
Bled down pressure above ASV to 10 bar to put 260 bar differential across ASV, bled back 160 liters. Maintained ~90 bar in tubing. Inflow tested ASV for 30 mins - ok.
Equlized accross ASV by pressuring up on A-annulus to 270 bar, pumped 220 liters. Bled off annulus pressure to zero. Bled off pressure on tubing from 90 bar to zero.
Disconnected cement hose from cement manifold. Released THRT by 9 clokwise turn and picked up 1 m. Secured cement hose on landing string.
Displaced landing string and riser to seawater pumping 15 m3 at 2000 lpm. Rigged down cement line. POOH with THRT and detached control lines from same.
Broke THRT from landing string. Broke landing string and laid down 2 x pup and 1 full joint.
Rig down and removed tubing running equipment, sheaves and reels from drillfloor.
Made up BPV setting tool. RIH with BPV and set same at 20,4 m MD according to Vetco instructions. POOH with BPV setting tool and laid down same.
RIH with 5 1/2" DP stand to 19,5 m MD. Attached air hose fitting to 1502 hub on standpipe. Displaced riser to air.
Held handover meeitng / toolbox prior to nippling down diverter, BOP and riser.
Laid out tubing single and 2 x pups form landing string. Undid nuts on slick joint.
Removed master bushing and outer ring from rotary.
Changed to 5" inserts in elevator to accommodate conductor housing pulling tool. Released mechanical seals on overshot.
Installed 10" split inserts in diverter.  Picked up diverter release tool. Not able to engage and release diverter.
Attempted several times to engage and release diverter - negative. Laid down diverter release tool.
Removed elevator and attached slings to bails. Pulled diverter using slings and set back same.
Pulled overshot joint using slings. Installed outer ring and masterbushing.
Dismanteled BOP tension cylinder and pulled aside. Racked back overshot joint. Cleared drillfloor for pulling BOP riser joint.
Disconnected NT-2 on BOP. Installed cradle in HTS. Installed slings for pulling riser BOP riser joint.
Skidded BOP to stb storage. Attached 2 ea 10 MT slings to BOP riser joint padeyes.
Disconnected BOP riser joint NT-2 on wellhead. Removed scaffolding on weather deck.
Removed scaffloding on weather deck. Removed split hatches in weather deck. Removed masterbushing. Confirmed well F-4 shut in with no pressure. Picked up riser and drained out seawater inside.
Held toolbox talk prior to pulling riser.
Pulled BOP riser through wellhead moudule, moonpool and rotary. Laid out riser on HTS cradle.
Installed and secured hatch on weather deck. Installed dart in BPV.

Removed communication collar and unwrapped control lines as required. Fitted graphoil seals and fed control lines through dedicated ports in wellhead. Made up external fittings on control lines to energize graphoil seals. Installed VG137 seal on multibowl and VG63 seal on top of tubing hanger. Filled void with hydraulic oil. Meanwhile cleaned and tidied wellhead and prepared for lifting down XMT spool.

Transferred and installed XMT spool on wellhead according to Vetco instructions. Made up NT-2 connector. Energized BT seal pumping plastic sealant through port #7/#8 (up to 5000 psi). Tested VG63 seal by applying 500 psi through port #9/#10. Tested TH void through test port #5/#6 to 345 bar / 15 min - ok.

Meanwhile attached slings onto TDS bails for lifting XMT.
Picked up XMT with port overhead crane in moonpool and landed XMT on Weatherdeck. Transferred XMT to slings from drillfloor. Backed up lift sideways using 6 T moonpool tugger.
Removed F-9 hatch and beam for passing through XMT.
Lifted XMT though weather deck and placed onto spool pice on XMT deck. Orientated tree according to instructions from Vecto/production dept. Made up Graylock connection.

Installed hatches on weatherdeck. Pressure tested seal ring between spool and XMT to 35 bar / 10 min through test ports #3 and #4. Installed teflon seal rings and made up exit blocks for hydraulic lines.

Installed exit block for DHPG control ine. Had problems with broken allen bolt, installed new bolt. Tested exit block to 10000 psi according to WD procedure - not able to get good test. Discussed situation - test in SH procedure specified 5000 psi test. Re-tested exit block to 5000 psi, but still not able to get good test. Broke off exit block and removed excess paint from WH and exit block. Polished exit block seal surface. Installed exit block, hooked up Vetco pump with recorder and tested exit block to 500/5000 psi 5/10 min -ok. 

Meanwhile pulled and laid down diverter.

Spliced DHPG cable. Made up DHPG wellhead outlet to exit block according to WD procedure. Pressure tested wellhead outlet -  negative. Observed leakage around threads between wellhead outlet and exit block. Dismanteled wellhead outlet and found damage on primary metal seal around threads. Discussed situation. Decided to go ahead with XMT hook up activities.

Meanwhile serviced TDS.
Installed flow spool on XMT with tugger support from drillfloor according to instructions from production.

Made up XMT flow spool with hy-torq kit. Worked to hook up coflex hose to wellhead module production hub. Used slings, chainhoists and eagle clamps as required to support/jack coflex hose. 

Meanwhile hung off travelling block for 6 month maintenance of crown block.
Hooked up coflex hose to hub in wellhead module. Made up clamp with Hy-torq kit.
Removed hatches and transferred flowline support bracket to XMT deck. Installed hatches

Removed DHPG wellhead outlet. Cut and reterminated DHPG conductor. Replaced seals and re-installed DHPG wellhead outlet according to WD procedure. Tested wellhead outlet through exit block to 345 bar / 10 min - ok. Hooked up DHPG to wellhead junction box. Found that flow spool on XMT had wrong allignement.
Broke bolts on flowline spool. Re-alligned flowline spool.
Installed flowline hub support bracket on XMT. Found that it was the wrong bracket, even though it was marked F-14.
Reverted to testing hydraulic control lines. Hooked up BOT pump. Tested DHSV line and exit block to 570 bar / 15 min - ok. Tested ASV line and exit block to 570 bar / 15 min - ok.
Removed chain hoists and slings from flowlines and repalced with 5 MT chainhoists and slings.
Removed wellhead bracket from XMT and put on weatherdeck. Meanwhile cut bolt holes in F-14 support bracket in mechanical workshop.
Rigged chainblocks and slings in moonpool for supporting tugger when pulling in coflex flowline Made up bolts on flow spool with Hy-torq kit.

Pulled/jacked coflex flowline hose using chain hoists, slings and tugger from drillfloor. Brought modified support bracket to XMT deck. Installled support bracket on XMT.

Meanwhile serviced fwd PRS.
Jacked coflex flowline hub in place and made up graylock clamp with handtools.

Made up bolts on graylock clamp with Hy-torq kit. Attmepted to fit support bracket shoe/clamp - observed to narrow angle/gap between support bracket and shoe/clamp. Discussed situation- decided to continue operation as modification of the shoe/clamp would be needed. Suspended flowline in 2 ea 5 MT slings/chainhoists. Removed tugger from flowline. Removed kill line on F-12 and moved to F-14. Flushed packer fluid from cement unit and displaced line to drillwater. Pulled hydraulic line from well control panel to XMT deck. Installed hatches and cover.

Meanwhile serviced TDS and drawworks.

Held toolbox talk prior to XMT bodytest and filling coflex flowline. Lined up cement unit. Performed line test against closed kill wing valve 30/345 bar 5 /10 min - ok. Opened kill wing valve, hydraulic master valve and manual master valve. Vented flowline on flow spool. Performed body test of XMT to 30/345 bar 5/10 min - ok. Lined up for filling coflex flowline from cement unit.
Lined up for filling coflex flowline. Filled coflex flowline with drillwater pumping from cement unit via KWV and HWV on XMT.
Held handover meeting / toolbox. Prepared for pulling dart and BPV.
Made up BPV retrieval rod. Pulled BPV and dart.
Transferred Well Dynamics pump to wellhead. Ran DHSV control hose from hydraulic panel in moonpool.

Performed line test agains KWV to 30 bar / 5 min - ok. Attempted to test coflex flowline to 99 bar. Pressured up on cement unit. Walked lines and observed leakage in production manifold system.

Meanwhile prepared for running WL.

Attached hydrualic control hoses from well control panel to DHSV exit block and HMV actuator. Made up WD chemical injection manifold on wellhead. Re-arranged WD test pump and hooked up to checmical injection mainfold. Opened KWV and HMV from local control panel.

Meanwhile prepared for running WL.

Pressured up tubing to 35 bar and opened DHSV. Continued to pressure up on tubing to 220 bar / (750 liters). Closed LMV and bled off pressure above to 5 bar. Observed inflow test for 10 min - ok. Pressured up chemical injection line while maintaining pressure on tubing - held test for 10 min -  ok. Equalize across LMV and opened same.

Meanwhile prepared for running WL.
Closed HMV and bled off pressure above to 5 bar. Inflow tested HMV for 10 min - ok.

Bled of tubing pressure while maintaining pressure on chemical injection line. Observed rupture disc shearing at 70 bar tubing pressure. Chemical injection line pressure stabilized at ~50 bar. Pressured up on tubing to 100 bar to confirm checmical injection check valve holding - ok.
Closed KWV, SHV and HMV. Rigged down testing equipment.
Installed XMT cap.

Commissioned XMT.

Meanwhile prepared for running WL : 
-Re-arranged toolcatcher
-Bulit grease injection
-Built cable head
-Checked and tested equipment

Comissioned XMT. Tested coflex hose 100 bar / 15 min - test approved by production.

Meanwhile prepared for running WL :

-Performed service on drawwork
-Cleaned and tidied drillfloor
-Removed support bracket from flowline for modifications
-Checked and tested equipment
-Made up lubricator sections on cantilever
-Spotted grease injection skid and well control skid on drillfloor

Commissioned XMT.

Meanwhile :
-Dismantled IBOPs
-Maintenance on diverter
-Mounted and commissioned manrider on drillfloor
-Cleaned lower shakers
-Performed derrick inspection

Commissioned XMT.

Meanwhile :
-Installed WL riser spool / x-over on XMT.
-Installed WL BOP's
-Fitted hole cover around WL riser spool on weatherdeck

Commissioned XMT.

Meanwhile :
-Mounted IBOPs
-Prepared for running WL
-Cleaned in drilling areas

Commissioned XMT.

Meanwhile :
-Tested IBOP.s to 30345 bar 5/10 min - ok
-Spotted WL BOP control unit
-Built sacffolding around WL BOPs in moonpool
-Hooked up and functioned WL BOPs
-Ran WL riser and connected to WL BOPs
-Tested/checked WL logging tools and WL tractor
-Rigged lo-torques and check valve on F-14 XMT

Meanwhile :
-Cleaned drillfloor
-Maintenance on diverter
-Tidied in moonpool and wellhead module
